description.plain:
Born on August 30, 1989, Bleta Rexha–widely known by her stage name Bebe Rexha, with Bebe meaning “bumblebee”–is an American singer and songwriter hailing from Brooklyn, New York. Her Albanian background and passion for music at the young age of 4 led her to pursue her love for music through Tottenville High School on Staten Island.

She is best known for being featured on the hit singles “Take Me Home” by Cash Cash, “Hey Mama” by David Guetta and “Me, Myself and I” by G-Eazy. She is also known for being the lead vocalist of the American band Black Cards, which was created by Pete Wentz, lead bassist of Fall Out Boy.

She has worked producing and writing for several different artists and most notably co-wrote the number-one US Billboard Hot 100 hit “The Monster” by Eminem featuring Rihanna.

She published two EPs in 2017: All Your Fault Pt. 1 & Pt. 2. “Meant To Be”, which is in part 2, has entered US Billboard Hot 100 and is the longest No.1 on the Billboard Hot Country songs.

“Meant To Be” would also be later included in Bebe’s debut album Expectations, the latter being released on June 22, 2018. The album peaked at #13 on the Billboard Hot 200.

On May 7th, 2021, Bebe’s highly anticipated second studio album, Better Mistakes, was released. It consisted of more personal outlook on music, and featured many A-list artists, including Travis Barker, Lil Uzi Vert, and Doja Cat.

description.plain:
“Meant to Be” is the closing track on Bebe Rexha’s third EP, All Your Fault: Pt. 2 and the lead single from her debut studio album, Expectations. Initially released as the EP’s second single, it is a country-pop track with a que-sera-esque message.

Featuring country duo Florida Georgia Line, the track was produced by Willshire and written by Tyler Hubbard (of FGL), Rexha, David Garcia and Josh O. Miller. The song was noted by many critics as a surprise collaboration, and further solidified her recognition as a diverse recording artist.

The single is Bebe’s most successful as a solo artist, peaking at #2 on the Billboard Hot 100 and #1 on the country charts. “Meant to Be” marks Rexha’s third top 10 song (and Florida Georgia Line’s second) on the Hot 100.

songs.full_title: I'm a Mess by Bebe Rexha
songs.title: I’m a Mess

description.plain:
“I’m a Mess” sees Bebe Rexha making self-disparaging statements about her state of being while at the same time expressing optimism for the future. The electro-pop song was released as a single ahead of Bebe’s album Expectations.

The chorus of this song features a musical interpolation of 90’s pop-rock song’s chorus- “Bitch” by Meredith Brooks. The writer of the aforementioned song, Shelly Pieken posted on instagram, confirming the writers of “I’m a Mess” had given her a co-writing credit, after making the connection:

Guess what! It’s my birthday. And guess what I got? A nice little gift. The writers of Bebe Rehxa’s “I’m a Mess” (Justin Trantor, Jussifer & Devon Corey), did a classy thing when they suspected the song ‘interpolated’ “Bitch.” They gave me a co-writing credit. :) #ClassActs Now can I have my cake?

Bebe Rexha revealed on twitter that this song featured her favorite lyrics from her album Expectations. She also tweeted out snippets of the lyrics before it’s release.

description.plain:
“The Way I Are” is a song from Bebe Rexha’s album, “All Your Fault Pt. 2”, which was released 19 May 2017.

About the song, Bebe said:

“It’s a f-you song to the record label. When you’re developing as an artist you have to kinda fight the stereotype of what everybody’s expecting of you, what way you should be, how you should look, what color your hair should be, how your make up should be and what you should wear. But the most important thing is if you like you and if you like the way you look”.
